thread.title: New hangar at Air Force museum gets first aircraft
thread.title_full: New hangar at Air Force museum gets first aircraft | The Columbus Dispatch

author: Dayton Daily News
title: New hangar at Air Force museum gets first aircraft
text:
DAYTON — Joe Engle hadn’t for half a century climbed into the cockpit of a hypersonic X-15 rocket plane that cruised to the edge of space.
But the 83-year-old retired Air Force test pilot and the record-setting aircraft were brought together recently when the X-15 became the first plane towed into a new, privately funded $40.8 million gallery expansion at the National Museum of the U.S. Air Force.
To read more, visit the website of the Dayton Daily News .
